FORMATTING RULES:
- Use Roman numerals (I., II., III.) for main topics
- Use capital letters (A., B., C.) for subtopics
- Use Arabic numerals (1., 2., 3.) for detailed items
- Main section headers in ALL CAPS
- Subsection headers in Title Case
- Do NOT use markdown, code blocks, or backticks
- Do NOT use ## or # headers
- Use plain text with careful spacing for hierarchy
- Keep it left aligned always

SPECIAL FORMATTING FOR MOTIONS/VOTES:
- For motion items with voting lines (1st, 2nd, VOTE), format them as single continuous lines
- Example: "Motion to approve... | 1st ___ 2nd ___ | VOTE: [initials] ___"
- Use pipe (|) or dash (-) separators to keep voting elements together
- Do NOT use excessive spacing or indentation that could trigger code block rendering
- Alternative format: "Motion text [1st ___ | 2nd ___ | VOTE: ___]"

CONTENT REQUIREMENTS:
- Include specific times/durations if mentioned in source
- Group logically related items together
- Maintain formal corporate/governmental tone
- Be concise while preserving all important details
